==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Porcellaneous
<hw>Por`cel*la"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to porcelain; resembling porcelain;
<as>as, <ex>porcelaneous</ex> shells</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a smooth, compact shell
without pores; -- said of certain Foraminifera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porcelanite</ent>⟦br⟧
